        <p>
            Arrays are like variables but they contain multiple values. This can be usefull when we want to list every user in our website. This is how it would work:
        </p>
        <div class="code">
            names = ["xNotKing", "iDev90G", "Paradise", "Infinity"]
        </div>
        <p>Let's print 'Infinity' in our terminal. In order to do this we've to know that the first value on an array is not 1, it is 0. Now if we want to print Infinity we must count: xNotKing = 0 iDev90G = 1 Paradise = 2 Infinity = 3. Now to print the value we must follow this syntax: </p>
        <div class="code">
            names = ["xNotKing", "iDev90G", "Paradise", "Infinity"]<br>
            print(names[3])
        </div>
